               <p>MR. BARRY conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-296-person2495">
                  JONATHAN 
                  MOORE
               <interp inst="t18300415-296-person2495" type="surname" value="MOORE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-296-person2495" type="given" value="JONATHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-296-person2495" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a servant to Mr. Thomas Frith; he is a <rs id="t18300415-296-viclabel1614" type="occupation">block ironmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-296-victim2494 t18300415-296-viclabel1614"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18300415-296-crimeloc1615">High Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-296-crimeloc1615" type="placeName" value="High Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-296-crimeloc1615" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-296-off1612 t18300415-296-crimeloc1615"></join>. On the 22nd of February the prisoner came for a pair of butt hinges - he told me to make the holes larger; he was walking about the shop - I watched him, and saw him go to the partition where the finger-plates were kept in parcels, which are marked; he took a parcel, and put it under his apron - my master's son was in the shop; we went to him, found the plates under his arm, and my master's son took them from him - I saw him take them from the partition; we have lost a great many of these articles.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. He found nothing on me at all. Witness. Yes, I did, under his apron.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-296-person2496">
